column17: 志愿者您好！我叫郝雨歌，今年秋天将要去杜克读经济学硕士，未来的目标是读PhD，所以接下来的一年是很关键的一年。不过，我也觉得“既然决定要出来，那也要过的开心”，所以十分期待接下来一年的学习和课余生活。平时的乐趣有交换明信片，去电影院看电影，还有打麻将（因为在四川读的本科，所以耳濡目染就学会并且喜欢上了）。目前也在尝试加入字幕组做字幕，希望这能成为我的新一个爱好。虽然来到了美国，但是对欧洲仍然有难以割舍的执念，所以希望以后能去欧洲读PhD，即使我的老师跟我说欧洲更难毕业╮(╯▽╰)╭。总之，很高兴能加入到杜克这个大家庭，也希望能和更多的人成为朋友。最后，真诚地感谢学长学姐们的志愿接机，你们辛苦了！ / Hello volunteers! My name is Hao Yuge and I am going to attend the graduate school this fall to pursue a master degree in Economics. My objective is to apply for a decent PhD program so that the next year will be very critical for me. However, I also hold the thought that if I am going to spend the next two years in US, I should live a happy life in the next two years. Therefore I'm looking forward to my life in Duke. My hobbies include swapping postcards, going to cinema, and Mahjong( a chess game which is very popular in Sichuan Province. I learned and got fond of it when I attended my undergraduate in Sichuan Province). At present I join a team which makes caption for funny video and I hope this would be my new hobby. Although I decided to come to US to pursue my master degree, I still have a crush on Europe and I hope I could attend a PhD program in Europe, even if my teacher told me that it is harder for PhD student to graduate in Europe╮(╯▽╰)╭. Anyway, I am very happy to join the Duke community and I hope to make more friends. I sincerely want to express my gratitude to those volunteers. Thank you!
